\N<Man>Segi-san, where do you think you're going? I have a bad
feeling about this, but if you're planning to go to the
ruins ahead, I'd advise against it.

\N<Man>Even the entrance management of the ruins that have been in
this town for ages is now handled by Ryuda's soldiers...
<ActiveMessage:\C[10]■EV発生■>
\N<Segi>Um...
\N<Rozaro>Hm? What is it, Segi-san?

\N<Segi>Actually, I saw the request board at the management
office... Rozaro-san's.

\N<Rozaro>Request board? Ah, you mean about the sparring partner. What
about it?
\N<Segi>...Well, I was wondering if I might be of any help to you?
\N<Rozaro>You, Segi-san?

\N<Segi>Yes, I am aware that I might not be strong enough to be your
sparring partner.

\N<Segi>But you have always been a great help to me and my son, and
more than anything, it would serve as training for myself as
well.

\N<Segi>I know it's selfish of me to offer to help with training
when in the end, it's for my own benefit.
\N<Segi>But... what do you think? Could I be of any help to you?

\N<Rozaro>...Understood. Then I'll accept your offer without
reservation.
\N<Segi>Really? Thank you so much. I'll do my very best.

\N<Rozaro>Of course, I'll pay you for your time as a training partner.
But since it's training, I can't hold back. Is that alright
with you?
\N<Segi>Yes, of course.

\N<Rozaro>Hmm, then let's start in the forest on the outskirts as soon
as you're ready.
\N<Segi>Understood, thank you very much.
air07
\N<Rozaro>Then, Segi-san, shall we start the training right away?
\N<Segi>Yes, thank you very much.
i_1_セギ03aa
\N<Segi>Ha, haa... haa...
\N<Rozaro>...
i_1_セギ03a

\N<Rozaro>...Segi-san, don't overdo it. You should rest a bit. You're
not ready to spar with me just yet.
\N<Segi>No, I'm fine... What should I... help with next...

\N<Rozaro>...I appreciate the sentiment. But if we've managed to find
this time, I want it to be meaningful for you as well.

\N<Rozaro>In other words... I want this training to be beneficial for
you too, not just for me.
\N<Segi>Eh...?

\N<Rozaro>So from here on out, let's make it training for your sake.
Consider it part of my request to you, is that okay?
\N<Segi>Rozaro-san... Thank you very much.

\N<Rozaro>Don't thank me just yet. Of course, I'll take it seriously
since I'm involved. Make sure you don't regret agreeing to
train with me later.
\N<Segi>Yes... but, I'll do my best...

\N<Rozaro>Hmm... Listen, Segi-san. As a warrior who must fight, there
are several key elements you're critically lacking.

\N<Rozaro>One is muscular strength, which is the source of power for
attacks. Another is stamina, essential for defense against
attacks. And one more is vitality, the essence of life.

\N<Rozaro>All are important elements in battle. Now, what do you
consider important? Choose any, and I'll accompany you in
that training.

\N<Segi>(Indeed, all the elements Rozaro-san mentioned seem
important... Which one should I choose...)
Muscle (Attack Increase)
Stamina (Defense Increase)
Vitality (Max HP Increase)
筋力(攻撃力上昇)

\N<Rozaro>You're focusing on muscular strength. Understood. Then let's
proceed with today's training in that manner.

\N<Rozaro>If you feel like it, please let me know again. I'm always
